scene.message:
Maki: Your school's gym is{nl}
new, right? Does it have{nl}
club rooms and all?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Honestly, how{nl}
antiquated. It wouldn't{nl}
surprise me if it collapsed{nl}
any moment.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: The curtains are full of{nl}
holes — heh, you could peep{nl}
easy in here{wait_fr:48}... I'm kidding!{waitkey}I wouldn't peep, not me!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: The more I look at this{nl}
town, the stranger it is.{nl}
It's truly like a world of{nl}
the past.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Tch, what a dump. They{nl}
should just tear this place{nl}
down too, and quick!{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: I haven't got time to{nl}
tag along on your little{nl}
stroll.{waitkey}{ret}

Student: Captain~!{wait_fr:21} I want a{nl}
club room for the ballet{nl}
club~!{waitkey}With a club room, we wouldn't{nl}
get peeped on while changing!{waitkey}{ret}
